Coca-Cola, Johnson & Johnson share losses lead Dow's nearly 100-point drop

Shares of Coca-Cola and Johnson & Johnson are posting losses Thursday morning, sending the Dow Jones Industrial Average into negative territory. Shares of Coca-Cola KO, +0.12% and Johnson & Johnson JNJ, -0.84% are contributing to the blue-chip gauge's intraday decline, as the Dow DJIA, +0.52% was most recently trading 96 points (0.5%) lower. Coca-Cola's shares have declined $2.63, or 5.9%, while those of Johnson & Johnson have fallen $6.76 (5.0%), combining for a roughly 64-point drag on the Dow. Other components contributing significantly to the decline include United Technologies UTX, Procter & Gamble PG, -0.06%, and Pfizer PFE, -0.48%. A $1 move in any one of the 30 components of the index results in a 6.78-point swing.

